<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 2 Apr 2003
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: OIE Alert [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/030331BRA.htm>

(Date of previous outbreak of scrapie in Brazil reported to the OIE: March
2001).
Translation of information received on 28 Mar 2003 from Dr Joao Crisostomo
Mauad Cavallero, Director, Department of Animal Protection (DDA), Ministry
of Agriculture, Livestock and Food Supply, Brasilia:
Location of the outbreak: Fazenda Rio Grande district, region of Curitiba,
State of Parana.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and histopathological.
Date of confirmation of diagnosis: 27 Mar 2003.
Estimated date of first infection: 21 Jan 2003.
Total number of animals in the outbreak: 123 sheep.
No. of cases: 1.
No. of animals destroyed: 1.
No. of animals slaughtered: 0.
Control measures: quarantine of the affected farm.
Animal Health Information Department Office international des epizooties
(OIE) <information.dept@oie.int>
Further details will be published in the next issue of Weekly Disease
Information, available on line as of Friday 4 Apr 2003 afternoon (GMT).
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Scrapie is a TSE (transmissible spongiform encephalitis) of sheep, just as
BSE (mad cow disease) is a TSE of cattle. Scrapie has been recognised for
200 years, and has not been shown to cause human illness. It is an OIE LIst
B disease for which reporting is only required annually. - Mod.JW]
